						<summary>

						<p>On pillar No. 1 of the Pātāḷa-Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kāki Appayyadēva-mahārāja, A.D. 1525.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="italic">Pārthiva, Pushya,</hi> śu. 3, Sunday, probably corresponding to A.D. 1525, December 17.</p>						

						<p>Registers a gift of wet land and 2 <hi rend="italic">tūmu</hi> of dry land by Timmi-śeṭṭi, son of Vuppara Pegaḍaśeṭṭi to Tipana, son of Chinta Chenne-bōya for his having constructed the wall round the temple of Kēśava-perumāḷ.</p>						

						</summary>
